data.text: Great meeting with labor leaders in Duluth today. As I said to them, when unions are strong, our economy is strong. And when our economy is strong, Minnesota is strong. https://t.co/WsytFuImP3
ICE has no place in our schools. I joined Duluth Public Schools Superintendent John Magas, school board members, and staff today in Duluth. https://t.co/vr4oesf5Iq

The Winter Olympics are officially underway. I couldn’t be prouder of the 28 Minnesotans that will be competing, the second most of any state.

Let’s bring home the gold!🏅🇺🇸 https://t.co/gOd66XYacW
ICE is wreaking havoc on Minnesota’s economy and costing our local businesses millions of dollars every week. This cannot go on. ICE needs to leave immediately. https://t.co/Peh2uZcoQA

Noem calls legal Haitians leeches. They win in court. 

“The Haitian plaintiffs include a neuroscientist researching Alzheimer’s, a bank’s software engineer, a lab assistant in toxicology, a college economics major and a nurse. No leeches joined the suit.” https://t.co/3K70tTjTik

I met with the Board of the Minnesota State Association of Narcotics Investigators to discuss how we can better protect Minnesotans. We must ensure law enforcement has the resources they need to take on the dangerous drugs like meth and fentanyl. https://t.co/CCS0er2wK8

Sheriffs and local law enforcement officers put their lives on the line every day to keep us safe.

I’m honored to receive the Legislator of the Year award from the Major County Sheriffs of America and will keep working together to protect Minnesotans across our state. https://t.co/7ds7S4WO2Q

ICE is disrupting every aspect of life for so many Minnesotans and hurting our small businesses and local economies. Minnesota is coming together to shop local and support our small businesses, but what we really need is ICE out of our state.

https://t.co/YobFkgyh63

Over 300 former prosecutors are urging DOJ to allow independent local & state investigations into the killings of Renee Good and Alex Pretti.
